name: Santa Claus Journal, Vintage Santa Journal, St. Nicholas Journal and Diary
description:
This interactive journal will delight your kids or grandkids. Secret pockets hold mini file folders which contain Christmas-y postcards where all important wish lists may be written and "sent" to that special post office box located at the North Pole.

The journal is a construction of 20 pages of reinforced card stock covered in vintage images of Santa. Each Santa is engaged one of his many important and TOP SECRET Christmas tasks. The pages of the journal are embellished with paper word ruffles dipped in twinkle glitter or highlighted by Chritmas paper flags. Each Santa in the journal has a glitter beard. The journal has a distinctly vintage feel. It is full of nostalgia and feels cozy and warm, like a cup of cocoa.

Two secret pockets hold mini file folder stuffed TO THE GILLS with postcards that will serve to record those crucial Christmas lists to Santa. This journal will become a treasured family tradition and keepsake. I always enclose photo corners with every order which can be used to attach a lasting memory from this oh, so special holiday.

So, up on the rooftop, you better look out, God bless us everyone, be sure to order your journal early enough to record all of your most precious memories this Christmas and holiday season.

8.5" x 6" in size. Decorated with glitter and sparkly jewel brads. A delight.


Thank you for looking.

You can see all my other journals and tags by entering the rest of my shop. All papers are original and are my own digital design collages. I use images that I either own or lease or have purchased. Thanks to depositphoto and clipart.com. I have many additional pictures. 

https://dorothyjane.bigcartel.com

name: Jane Austen Journal, The Original
description:
The original. I conceived the idea of the Jane Austen Journal one day while I was re-reading Mansfield Park. I was so excited about my idea, I began designing the pages of the journal, pulling together scrap book techniques I had learned with my collection of antique fashion plates. I imagined something which had an antique appearance combined with a fun, personal, interactive quality. It has been a little over a year since I made the first Jane Austen Journal and I want to offer this original curvy journal at the original price!

This delightful journal is the perfect place to dash off your thoughts. Each page is blank, some with lines, some embellished with word ruffles and paper flags that list each of Jane's novels. It is different from a traditional journal, it is only eight pages long and would make a very special gift to a fellow Janeite. Perhaps you could include pictures from your favorite book club gathering or record your trip to Chawton. 

Each journal comes with a two library pockets stuffed with journalling cards. You can place these pockets as you choose. Tuck a special thought into the hidden folder, or attach a picture with the photo corners that are included. Personalize your journal with your own handwriting and thoughts.

Several tags also come with the journal so that you can easily pop one in your purse to have handy for recording your thoughts and then easily returning them to the journal.

Unique and quite different. Designed to be a special, personalized gift or a concise place to save your special reflections.

The journal is one of a kind. All papers are designed by myself and the art comes from my private collection of 19th century fashion plates. No two journals are exactly the same. They differ slightly in page arrangement and paper choice. But, each one is lovely all by itself! Please allow up to ten business days for assembly. This is the original Jane Austen Journal using images which I own - the idea conceived by me using scrapbooking techniques learned in many design classes. . Please ask for additional pictures. Thank you for looking!

Please visit the rest of my store here:  http://dorothyjane.bigcartel.com

name: Pride and Prejudice Journal, Jane Austen Bicentennial Journal
description:
Pride and Prejudice: A Jane Austen Mini Journal

This is the bicentennial anniversary of Pride and Prejudice, Jane Austen's most beloved novel.This is a sweet little pocket size journal that fits into even the most diminutive purse. 3 1/2" wide x 5 1/2" long. The cover is a facsimile of the front piece to the original novel (created by me, using reproduction antique fonts) which only states that it is written by the author of "Sense and Sensibility." 

The back features a fashion plate published within the same era if the novel. Perhaps Elizabeth Bennett dressed in a similar manner!

Inside, you will find a dear little library pocket, stuffed with journal cards marked with a precious little wren in filigree. 

There is also a back pocket, to hide your extra journaling cards.

The pages are unlined, so you may embellish your thoughts with pencil sketches of your travels.

Made from a moleskin and re-covered . Designed by myself.

name: London Travel Journal, London Old Maps Journal, Travel and Adventure Journal
description:
This London Travel Journal looks like it comes from the shelves of the London Library. Reminiscent of the books of Dickens and Hardy, this journal is a subtle tribute to one of the most loved and visited cities in the world.

This travel journal is filled with secret pockets, hidden corners, and comes with a journal within a journal. There are numerous journaling cards secreted away in the mini file folders which fit securely in the two hidden pockets. There are pages embellished with torn vintage book page pleats. Six aged studs grace the cover. The cover is actually a reproduction made form book end covers of old, marbled paper.

The journal has many surprises:  8" x 6" - it is sturdy and plump with features. Depending on how you count the pages, there are 8 single sided spaces or 16 double. I always send photo corners with which you may attach your signature photos from your trip to any of the pages in the journal. The large 80 page, lined Moleskine kraft journal is embedded into the center of the journal.

Images used in the collages which comprise the pages of the journal are architectural blueprint elevations of St. Paul's Cathedral, a London bookshop, a vintage map of Central London, a Restoration period map of old London, and commemorative stamp of the Greenwich Meridian. 

The journal cards are ample and perfect to take with you on a special excursion and then return to the journal later for safe keeping.

Like a treasure chest, this journal is packed with hidden gems. Perfect for your adventure.

All papers are original and are my own digital design collages. I use images that I either own or lease or have purchased. Thanks to depositphoto and clipart.com. I have many additional pictures. Thank you for looking.

There are other journals back in my shop: 

https://dorothyjane.bigcartel.com

name: Bird Watcher Diary, Travel Nature Nest Log, Bird Eggs, Personal Travel Log,
description:
Are you a bird lover? I have created a very simple journal to place your bird sketches or poetry about our lovely flying friends. Perhaps a bird has made a nest right outside your kitchen window or on the stoop outside your urban apartment and you are inspired to record the activities of the bird family. This journal will allow you to dash off a simple thought or impression.

Made from card stock with vintage bird and nest images. I have created soft, digital collages for the papers used in the journal. Using pages from cast off paper back books which I find in the dollar bin at a local book store, I create paper word ruffle embellishments. This journal is quite simple in its design and feel. The gentle, curvy bracket shape is pleasing and feminine. The spine is bound in silky, soft green ribbon, much like a bird would use if it came across some blowing off a little girl's braid ...

Done in soft, muted shades of pale aqua, pale blue, pale green and a shade close to that of willow bark, this journal is perfect for favorite quotes or random thoughts. The last page sports a simple library pocket with some journal cards for your extra long impressions and observances.

Thank you for looking.

name: Paris Travel Journal, Eiffel Tower Journal, Handmade Art Journal
description:
If you are planning a trip to Paris, or merely dreaming about the trip you may take one day, this unique journal is the perfect companion to help organize and preserve your memories or plans. Images from the Paris of the turn of the century and a bit later make this a special place to press a flower from the Tuileries or save a ticket stub from the Paris Opera House. Secret pockets and mini file folders labeled for various tourist activities are stuffed with special journaling tags and would make a great place to store receipts, postcards and destination stamps, all the ephemera from your trip. I know I love to save all my entrance stickers and tickets from the special trips I make. 

This version of the Paris travel journal DOES NOT include a Moleskine (there is a version which does for those who need to begin their novel while being inspired by Paris) but comes with secret pockets, and many journaling tags.

The colors used are soft turquoise, and aged beige and soft apricot. 

Each journal comes with three mini file folders stuffed with journalling tag and photo corners so that you may affix a special picture. Personalize your journal with your own handwriting and thoughts.

The journalling tags also accommodate a day of site seeing as you can easily pop one in your purse to have handy for recording your thoughts and then return it to the journal.

Unique and quite different. Designed to be a special, personalized gift or a concise place to save your special reflections.

The journal is one of a kind. All papers are designed by myself. I have many pictures, please ask if you would like to see more. 

The journal measures 8" x 6"

Each journal will be shipped up to one week after ordering to allow for assembly. Please allow 7 - 10 business days before shipping. This journal is particular needs to spend several days in the book press.
